01:00:39.745 --> 01:00:41.900
Here, we started off
by saying that this

01:00:41.900 --> 01:00:46.700
is a continuous
repetitive grating.

01:00:46.700 --> 01:00:49.640
And so we can think of it in
terms of a Fourier series.

01:00:49.640 --> 01:00:53.340
But of course, it's not
actually infinitely big.

01:00:53.340 --> 01:00:57.560
I guess it's not going to be
more than a few light years

01:00:57.560 --> 01:00:58.800
across.

01:00:58.800 --> 01:01:05.990
So this is multiplied by
another rect function, really.

01:01:05.990 --> 01:01:11.300
So the Fourier transform of this
whole thing multiplied by rect

01:01:11.300 --> 01:01:13.550
is something
convolved with a sinc.

01:01:13.550 --> 01:01:17.450
So each of these things is
not really a delta function.

01:01:17.450 --> 01:01:20.038
But it's really a
very narrow sinc,

01:01:20.038 --> 01:01:21.746
which depends on the
size of our grating.

01:01:21.746 --> 01:01:22.246
.

01:01:22.246 --> 01:01:24.590
So the point George
