01:24:07.090 --> 01:24:09.130
The intensity is
the second harmonic

01:24:09.130 --> 01:24:10.210
because of the squaring.

01:24:10.210 --> 01:24:12.790
And the contrast is 0.7.

01:24:12.790 --> 01:24:16.930
Right, so again we end up with
a bad image as it's shifted,

01:24:16.930 --> 01:24:19.270
because it's double frequency.

01:24:19.270 --> 01:24:22.060
And also, the contrast
is reduced in this case,

01:24:22.060 --> 01:24:26.410
because the strength of the
two beams was not the same.

01:24:26.410 --> 01:24:28.780
This is calculating
here the contrast.

01:24:28.780 --> 01:24:33.250
This is the normal definition
of contrast fringes--

01:24:33.250 --> 01:24:36.160
the difference over the sum.

01:24:36.160 --> 01:24:38.050
And it comes to 0.7062.

01:24:38.050 --> 01:24:43.630
In the previous case, of
